    "created_at": "2016-02-23T06:26:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-02-23T06:26:57Z",
    "body": "You can set the `ELECTRON_NO_ATTACH_CONSOLE` environment variable to disable console attachment, we are doing things in current way because most developers just want to have the output in console don't care about stdout. I don't think changing current behavior for uncommon use cases is a good idea.\n\nThe named pipe way is used by dualsubsystem which is mentioned in your comment, it works by redirecting output to named pipe, and then use a console program to read the named pipe and print data to stdout.\n"
  },
