    "created_at": "2017-01-25T03:09:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-01-25T03:09:15Z",
    "body": "I understand that the most common case mirrors console.log, but the fact that \"process.stdout.write doesn't write to the stdout\" is completely unintuitive - I'd be willing to bet that most developers who've tried to capture stdout from electron have run into this poor design choice, have had to run through the same merry-go-round of bug reports and QA-site posts, and have eventually circled back to complain that they're being given the run around."
